text: The Elks Temple in Boise, Idaho was built in 1914 in "Italian Palazzo Style". It has served as a clubhouse of the Benevolent and Protective Order of Elks (Elks) organization. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1978. ==References== Category:Buildings and structures in Idaho Category:Boise, Idaho Category:1914 establishments in the United States Category:1910s establishments in Idaho
title: Elks Temple (Boise, Idaho)
